Rules

  • Team Size: up to 4 team members allowed, but every player must have an account (No Account Sharing)
  • Flag Format: Use `BITSCTF{}` unless specified otherwise.
  • Fair Play: Adhere to all rules and maintain sportsmanship.
  • Respectful Behavior: Maintain respect and courtesy towards all.
  • No Sharing: Do not share flags, solutions, or post them online.
  • Dynamic Scoring: Sharing flags reduces points; score board is dynamic.
  • Limited Attempts: Some challenges have a limited number of attempts before they are locked.These challenges will not be unlocked again unless there is some error on Admin side(unlikely).
  • Pre-requisite Challenges: Some questions have a one or more follow up questions which only get unlocked on solving the preceeding challenges
  • Disqualification Rights: Organizers may disqualify for rule violations.
  • No Cheating: Cheating or gaining unfair advantage leads to disqualification.
  • Communication Etiquette: Use discord for questions; avoid unsolicited DMs/pings.
  • No Malicious Activity: Do not harm competition infrastructure or other systems.
  • Account Ownership: Each team member is required to have an individual account. Sharing accounts is forbidden.
  • The CTF competition begins on 16-02-2024 at 00:00 IST and lasts for 48 hours, ending on 18-02-2024 at 00:00 IST.
